Please note that Before delivery, we will conduct product quality and signal detection to ensure the intact function of the product. If you fail to receive the signal after installation and use, please exclude the following situations: Please check whether the GPS antenna interface is connected, and whether the connector is loose.Please check that the front of the GPS (black plastic shell) is facing up and facing the sky, and the back is facing down (with font face).Please check for interference sources, such as explosion-proof metal film affixed to the glass, other metal items, video cables, power cables and other installed electronic instruments.Please move the antenna to a few more positions for testing, such as the A-pillar, the lower right corner of the front windshield, the roof, and the upper right-view mirror. It is best to test in an open area. If you have any questions during installation or use, please let us know immediately and we will be happy to answer you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2021
reviews.reviewText: It works great. I DONT even have the antenna placed outside of the car and it still has full bars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought this because my 2010 Ralliart needed a GPS antenna. This so happened to fit just perfectly with my Land Nav GPS. Will be compatible with those screen 2008-2015. Not sure about 2015+ but as long as the plug is the same, you should be fine!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Immediately connected and works great!!!!
reviews.reviewText: Had it professionally installed in less than 15 minutes….worked perfectly and solved all the connectivity problems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does the job.
reviews.reviewText: Good quality item and will be installed 08/15/2023.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Low temp "freeze up"
reviews.reviewText: On a regular day this unit works perfectly. In single to 20's °F temps the unit fails to acquire satellites until it warms up. My antenna install located the unit just under my dash (thin top plastic cover), directly over the dash climate control vents. The proximity over the vents allows me to warm the unit up quickly. I cannot comment on how long it might take to warm up without the assistance of the heater vents close by.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits and works perfectly.
reviews.reviewText: Great price, fits my KENWOOD receiver just like the OEM. Thanks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Needs tweak to fit Toyota head unit
reviews.reviewText: Works like a champ. You will need to trim the square edges for it to fit in the standard Toyota head unit. The sides of the connector (along either side of the moving latch) need to be shaved down some, about 0.020". These are the square edges, not the rounded ones. (If looking at the face of the connector, it is shaped like a U, trim the tops of the U) Do not trim the latch. Otherwise it's perfect and fixed my GPS (2010 Highlander Limited/Nav).
